<file path="plans/260326-1147-spreadsheet-grid-component/phase-01-core-grid-setup.md">
# Phase 1: Core Grid Setup

## Context Links
- [Parent Plan](plan.md)
- [TanStack Research](research/researcher-01-tanstack-integration.md)
- [Architecture Brainstorm](../reports/brainstorm-260326-1147-spreadsheet-grid-architecture.md)

## Overview
- **Date:** 2026-03-26
- **Priority:** P1
- **Status:** done (critical/high fixes applied, medium deferred to later phases)
- **Review:** complete — see `plans/reports/code-review-260326-1258-phase-01-core-grid.md`
- **Description:** Bootstrap project, set up Vite + React 19 + TypeScript, implement core grid rendering with TanStack Table + Virtual, sorting, filtering, and virtual scrolling for 50k rows.

## Key Insights
- TanStack Table is headless — no DOM opinions. TanStack Virtual handles visible-range slicing.
- Row virtualizer wraps visible rows; column virtualizer is nested inside each row for horizontal virtualization.
- Overscan 10 rows / 2 columns is sweet spot. Memoization more impactful than overscan tuning.
- CSS variables for column widths (not inline styles) — prevents layout thrashing on resize.
- Sticky header must live outside virtualizer container to avoid disappearing on fast scroll.

## Requirements

### Functional
- F1.1: Render tabular data from array of objects
- F1.2: Virtual scrolling — row + column, handle 50k rows at 60fps
- F1.3: Single-column and multi-column sorting (click header to toggle)
- F1.4: Per-column filtering (text, number, date, select filters)
- F1.5: Global search filter
- F1.6: Pagination mode OR infinite scroll mode (configurable)

### Non-Functional
- NF1.1: First meaningful paint <500ms for 50k rows
- NF1.2: Scroll at 60fps on mid-range devices
- NF1.3: Bundle: core grid <50KB gzipped (excl. HyperFormula)
- NF1.4: All components <200 lines per file

## Architecture

### Data Flow
```
Props (data, columns) → useReactTable() → row/column models
  → useVirtualizer(rows) → visible row range
    → per-row useVirtualizer(columns) → visible cell range
      → CellRenderer (React.memo) → DOM
```

### Container Layout (3-pane for future pinned columns)
```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Column Headers (fixed, outside scroller) │
├────┬─────────────────────────────┬───────┤
│ L  │  Center (virtualized)       │  R    │
│ pin│  ← horizontal scroll →      │  pin  │
│    │  ↕ vertical scroll          │       │
├────┴─────────────────────────────┴───────┤
│ Status Bar                               │
└──────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Phase 1 only implements center pane; L/R pin added in Phase 2.

## Related Code Files

### Create
- `src/components/spreadsheet/spreadsheet-provider.tsx` — Zustand + HyperFormula context wrapper
- `src/components/spreadsheet/spreadsheet-grid.tsx` — Main grid container, layout
- `src/components/spreadsheet/virtual-grid.tsx` — TanStack Virtual viewport
- `src/components/spreadsheet/column-headers.tsx` — Header row (sorting UI)
- `src/components/spreadsheet/cell-renderer.tsx` — Display-only cell (memo'd)
- `src/stores/spreadsheet-store.ts` — Zustand store (UI state only)
- `src/types/spreadsheet-types.ts` — Core TypeScript interfaces
- `src/hooks/use-spreadsheet-store.ts` — Zustand selector hook
- `src/index.ts` — Public API barrel export
- `vite.config.ts`, `tsconfig.json`, `tailwind.config.ts`, `package.json`

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1: Project Bootstrap
1. `npm create vite@latest . -- --template react-ts`
2. Install deps: `@tanstack/react-table`, `@tanstack/react-virtual`, `zustand`, `immer`, `tailwindcss@4`, `zod`
3. Set up shadcn/ui (`npx shadcn@latest init`)
4. Configure path aliases (`@/` → `src/`)

### Step 2: Type Definitions
1. Define `CellValue`, `CellAddress`, `ColumnConfig`, `SpreadsheetState` in `spreadsheet-types.ts`
2. Define `SpreadsheetProps` — `data`, `columns`, `onCellChange`, `sortable`, `filterable`
3. Keep types generic: `SpreadsheetProps<TData extends Record<string, unknown>>`

### Step 3: Zustand Store
1. Create store with Immer middleware
2. Initial slices: `columns`, `activeCell`, `selectionRange`, `editingCell`, `sortingState`, `filterState`
3. Actions: `setActiveCell`, `setSelection`, `updateSorting`, `updateFilter`
4. No cell data in store — HyperFormula owns values (Phase 6 integrates; Phase 1 uses raw data)

### Step 4: SpreadsheetProvider
1. Create React context wrapping Zustand store
2. Accept `data` + `columns` props, initialize TanStack Table instance
3. Pass `table` instance via context (avoids prop drilling)

### Step 5: Virtual Grid
1. Create scroll container div with ref
2. Row virtualizer: `useVirtualizer({ count: table.getRowModel().rows.length, getScrollElement, estimateSize: () => 35, overscan: 10 })`
3. Column virtualizer: `useVirtualizer({ count: visibleColumns.length, horizontal: true, getScrollElement, estimateSize: (i) => columns[i].size ?? 120, overscan: 2 })`
4. Render only visible cells using both virtualizer ranges
5. Use `getItemKey` with stable row IDs (useCallback memoized)

### Step 6: Cell Renderer
1. `React.memo` component, receives `row`, `column`, `value`
2. Display-only in Phase 1 (editing in Phase 4)
3. Style via CSS variables: `--col-{id}-width`
4. Handle text overflow with ellipsis

### Step 7: Column Headers
1. Render header row outside scroll container (sticky)
2. Click to sort (single click = ASC, again = DESC, again = none)
3. Shift+click for multi-sort
4. Sort indicator icons (shadcn icons)

### Step 8: Sorting & Filtering
1. Wire TanStack Table `getSortedRowModel()`, `getFilteredRowModel()`
2. Column filter: render filter input in header dropdown
3. Global filter: debounced search input above grid
4. Custom filter functions for number ranges, date ranges

## Todo List

- [x] Project scaffold (Vite + React 19 + TS + Tailwind 4)
- [x] shadcn/ui initialization
- [x] TypeScript interfaces (`spreadsheet-types.ts`)
- [x] Zustand store with Immer (`spreadsheet-store.ts`)
- [x] SpreadsheetProvider context
- [x] TanStack Table integration (`spreadsheet-grid.tsx`)
- [x] Row virtualization
- [x] Column virtualization (nested, merged into `spreadsheet-grid.tsx`)
- [x] CellRenderer with React.memo
- [x] Column headers with sort UI
- [ ] Per-column filtering — **NOT DONE** (state wired, no UI)
- [x] Global search filter
- [ ] CSS variable column widths — **NOT DONE** (uses inline styles; deferred to Phase 2 resize)
- [ ] Pagination / infinite scroll toggle — **NOT DONE**
- [ ] Performance test: 50k rows scroll at 60fps — **NOT DONE** (no profiling run)

## Review Findings (fix before Phase 2)

- [x] **[Critical]** Memory leak: add unmount cleanup to `GlobalSearchFilter` timer ref
- [x] **[High]** `SpreadsheetContext` default value is `{} as StoreApi` — changed to `null`
- [ ] **[High]** Dual column virtualizers (grid + headers) can desync — defer to Phase 2 (shared scroll context)
- [x] **[High]** Remove no-op `useMemo(() => table, [table])` in `TableProvider`
- [ ] **[Medium]** Wire `rowHeight` prop or remove from `SpreadsheetProps` — defer to Phase 2
- [ ] **[Medium]** Fix ARIA role hierarchy — defer to Phase 7 (Polish)
- [x] **[Medium]** Add `getItemKey` to row virtualizer using stable row IDs
- [x] **[Medium]** Add ESLint config file (`eslint.config.js`)

## Success Criteria
- Grid renders 50k rows with <500ms initial paint
- Smooth 60fps scrolling (Chrome DevTools Performance audit)
- Sort + filter works on all column types
- All files <200 lines
- Clean TypeScript — no `any` types

## Risk Assessment

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|--------|------------|
| Nested virtualizers cause render thrashing | Medium | High | Profile early; fallback to row-only virtualization if columns <20 |
| TanStack Virtual + React 19 compat | Low | Medium | Pin versions; test with concurrent features off |
| Tailwind 4 breaking changes | Low | Low | Use stable release; check shadcn compat |

## Security Considerations
- No user-generated HTML in cells (XSS prevention) — always text content
- Sanitize filter inputs

## Next Steps
- Phase 2 (Column Management) depends on header rendering from this phase
- Phase 4 (Cell Editing) depends on CellRenderer + store from this phase
