# Phase 2: Column Management

## Context Links
- [Parent Plan](plan.md)
- [TanStack Research — Pinned Columns](research/researcher-01-tanstack-integration.md)
- [dnd-kit Research](research/researcher-02-hyperformula-zustand-dnd.md)
- Depends on: Phase 1 (core grid, headers)

## Overview
- **Date:** 2026-03-26
- **Priority:** P1
- **Status:** done
- **Review:** passed (4 issues fixed: critical visibility guard, CSS var sanitization, useCallback wraps, a11y attrs)
- **Review Report:** [code-review-260326-1309-phase-02-column-management.md](../reports/code-review-260326-1309-phase-02-column-management.md)
- **Description:** Column resize via drag handles, column reorder via dnd-kit, column pin/freeze (left + right using separate table containers), column visibility toggle.

## Key Insights
- Pinned columns: use separate table containers (left | center | right), NOT CSS sticky. Research confirms better virtual scrolling compat.
- dnd-kit dragged column must stay in DOM during drag — render outside virtual boundary via DragOverlay.
- Column reorder is UI-only concern; HyperFormula unaware of column display order.
- CSS variables for column widths avoid layout thrashing during resize.
- TanStack Table provides `getLeftVisibleCells()`, `getCenterVisibleCells()`, `getRightVisibleCells()` for pinned column rendering.

## Requirements

### Functional
- F2.1: Drag column border to resize; min-width 50px, max-width 800px
- F2.2: Drag column header to reorder (dnd-kit sortable)
- F2.3: Pin column to left or right via header context menu
- F2.4: Toggle column visibility via column menu or toolbar dropdown
- F2.5: Double-click resize handle to auto-fit column width to content

### Non-Functional
- NF2.1: Resize must not cause full grid re-render (CSS variables only)
- NF2.2: Drag overlay must show column preview at 50% opacity
- NF2.3: Pin/unpin must not break virtual scroll position

## Architecture

### Pinned Column Layout
```
┌────────┬────────────────────────────┬────────┐
│  LEFT  │     CENTER (virtualized)    │  RIGHT │
│ pinned │     ← scroll →              │ pinned │
│ fixed  │                             │ fixed  │
└────────┴────────────────────────────┴────────┘
```

Three `<table>` elements in a flex container. Left/right have `flex-shrink: 0`. Center has `overflow-x: auto` with column virtualization. Row heights sync via shared row virtualizer.

### Resize Data Flow
```
Mouse drag on handle → update CSS variable --col-{id}-width
  → onMouseUp: persist width to Zustand column config
  → TanStack Table column.size updates → virtualizer recalculates
```

### Reorder Data Flow
```
dnd-kit onDragEnd → reorder column array in Zustand
  → TanStack Table columnOrder state updates
  → Headers + cells re-render in new order
```

## Related Code Files

### Create
- `src/hooks/use-column-resize.ts` — Drag resize logic + CSS variable updates
- `src/components/spreadsheet/column-header-menu.tsx` — Sort/filter/hide/pin dropdown

### Modify
- `src/components/spreadsheet/column-headers.tsx` — Add resize handles, dnd-kit sortable, pin indicators
- `src/components/spreadsheet/spreadsheet-grid.tsx` — 3-pane layout (left | center | right)
- `src/components/spreadsheet/virtual-grid.tsx` — Center pane only; left/right render all their columns
- `src/stores/spreadsheet-store.ts` — Add columnOrder, pinnedColumns, columnVisibility slices
- `src/types/spreadsheet-types.ts` — Add PinPosition, ColumnVisibility types

### Install
- `@dnd-kit/core`, `@dnd-kit/sortable`, `@dnd-kit/utilities`

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1: Column Resize
1. Create `use-column-resize.ts` hook
2. Track mousedown on resize handle → mousemove updates CSS variable → mouseup persists
3. Use `requestAnimationFrame` for smooth resize (no React re-render during drag)
4. Update Zustand column config on mouseup only
5. Double-click handler: measure max content width via temporary off-screen render

### Step 2: Column Reorder (dnd-kit)
1. Wrap column headers in `<DndContext>` + `<SortableContext>`
2. Each header is `useSortable({ id: column.id })`
3. DragOverlay renders ghost header at 50% opacity
4. On `onDragEnd`: update `columnOrder` in Zustand store
5. Ensure dragged column renders outside virtual boundary during drag

### Step 3: 3-Pane Pinned Layout
1. Refactor `spreadsheet-grid.tsx` to flex container with 3 children
2. Left pane: `table.getLeftVisibleCells()` — fixed width, no scroll
3. Center pane: existing virtual-grid.tsx — horizontal + vertical virtualization
4. Right pane: `table.getRightVisibleCells()` — fixed width, no scroll
5. Sync vertical scroll across all 3 panes (shared scrollTop via ref)
6. Row virtualizer shared across panes (single source of visible row range)

### Step 4: Column Visibility
1. Add visibility toggle in `column-header-menu.tsx`
2. Use TanStack Table `columnVisibility` state
3. Toolbar dropdown showing all columns with checkboxes
4. Prevent hiding all columns (at least 1 must remain visible)

### Step 5: Column Header Menu
1. Create `column-header-menu.tsx` — shadcn DropdownMenu
2. Options: Sort ASC/DESC, Pin Left/Right/Unpin, Hide, Auto-fit width
3. Trigger on right-click or chevron icon click

## Todo List

- [x] `use-column-resize.ts` hook with CSS variable updates
- [x] Resize handles in column headers
- [x] Double-click auto-fit column width
- [x] dnd-kit integration for column reorder
- [x] DragOverlay ghost header
- [x] 3-pane layout (left-pinned | center | right-pinned)
- [x] Shared vertical scroll across panes
- [x] Pin column via header menu
- [x] Column visibility toggle (critical bug fixed)
- [x] Column header context menu (`column-header-menu.tsx`)
- [x] Zustand store: columnOrder, pinnedColumns, columnVisibility
- [x] Code review: critical & high severity fixes applied
- [x] Build verification: tsc + vite build pass

## Success Criteria
- Resize columns smoothly without grid re-render during drag
- Reorder columns via drag-and-drop with visual feedback
- Pin columns left/right; pinned columns stay fixed during horizontal scroll
- Toggle column visibility; at least 1 column always visible
- 50k rows still scroll at 60fps with 3 pinned columns

## Risk Assessment

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|--------|------------|
| 3-pane scroll sync lag | Medium | Medium | Use shared scrollTop ref + RAF |
| dnd-kit + virtual conflict | Medium | High | Render dragged column outside virtual boundary |
| Resize + sort interaction | Low | Low | Disable sort during resize drag |

## Security Considerations
- Column config changes are client-side only; no server validation needed
- Sanitize column IDs used as CSS variable names (alphanumeric + hyphen only)

