# Phase 5: Keyboard & Clipboard

## Context Links
- [Parent Plan](plan.md)
- Depends on: Phase 4 (cell editing, edit mode)

## Overview
- **Date:** 2026-03-26
- **Priority:** P1
- **Status:** pending
- **Review:** not started
- **Description:** Full keyboard navigation (arrows, Tab, Enter, Home/End, Page Up/Down), multi-cell selection (click+drag, Shift+click, Shift+arrow), copy/paste in TSV format (Excel-compatible).

## Key Insights
- Keyboard handler lives at grid container level; delegates to active cell.
- Arrow keys in display mode = navigate; in edit mode = cursor movement within editor. Enter exits edit mode + moves down.
- Multi-cell selection state: `{ start: CellAddress, end: CellAddress }` — renders highlight on all cells in range.
- Copy/paste uses `navigator.clipboard` API with TSV (tab-separated values) format for Excel compatibility.
- Paste into multi-cell selection: fill pattern or truncate to selection size.

## Requirements

### Functional
- F5.1: Arrow keys navigate between cells
- F5.2: Tab moves right; Shift+Tab moves left; wraps to next/prev row
- F5.3: Enter commits edit + moves down; Shift+Enter moves up
- F5.4: Home/End: first/last cell in row; Ctrl+Home/End: first/last cell in grid
- F5.5: Page Up/Down: scroll one viewport height
- F5.6: Click+drag to select cell range
- F5.7: Shift+click to extend selection from active cell
- F5.8: Shift+Arrow to extend selection one cell at a time
- F5.9: Ctrl+Shift+End to select to last cell
- F5.10: Ctrl+C copies selection as TSV; Ctrl+V pastes TSV into grid
- F5.11: Ctrl+X cuts selection (copy + clear values)
- F5.12: Ctrl+A selects all cells
- F5.13: Delete/Backspace clears selected cells

### Non-Functional
- NF5.1: Keyboard response <16ms (single frame)
- NF5.2: Selection highlight renders without full grid re-render
- NF5.3: Paste 1000 cells completes <100ms

## Architecture

### Keyboard Handler
```
Grid container onKeyDown
  → if editingCell: delegate to editor (arrows move cursor in input)
  → else:
    → Arrow/Tab/Enter: update activeCell in store
    → Shift+Arrow: extend selectionRange
    → F2/typing: enter edit mode
    → Ctrl+C/V/X: clipboard operations
    → Delete: clear selected cells
```

### Selection Model
```
Zustand state:
  activeCell: CellAddress          — current focus
  selectionRange: {                — highlighted range
    start: CellAddress,
    end: CellAddress
  } | null

Render: cells within range get .selected CSS class
  Active cell gets .active CSS class (distinct border)
```

### Clipboard Format
```
Copy: join selected cells row-by-row with \t (cols) and \n (rows)
Paste: split clipboard text by \n then \t → write to cells starting at activeCell
```

## Related Code Files

### Create
- `src/hooks/use-keyboard-navigation.ts` — Arrow/Tab/Enter/Home/End handlers
- `src/hooks/use-cell-selection.ts` — Click+drag, Shift+click, range management
- `src/hooks/use-clipboard.ts` — Ctrl+C/V/X handlers, TSV serialization

### Modify
- `src/components/spreadsheet/spreadsheet-grid.tsx` — Attach keyboard handler to container
- `src/components/spreadsheet/cell-renderer.tsx` — Selection highlight CSS classes
- `src/components/spreadsheet/virtual-grid.tsx` — Mouse event handlers for drag-select
- `src/stores/spreadsheet-store.ts` — Refine activeCell, selectionRange actions

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1: Keyboard Navigation Hook
1. Create `use-keyboard-navigation.ts`
2. Handle: ArrowUp/Down/Left/Right → move activeCell ±1
3. Tab → move right (wrap to next row); Shift+Tab → move left (wrap to prev row)
4. Enter → if editing: commit + move down; if not: enter edit mode
5. Home → first column in row; End → last column; Ctrl+Home → A1; Ctrl+End → last cell with data
6. PageUp/PageDown → move activeCell by viewport row count
7. F2 → enter edit mode on active cell
8. Typing alphanumeric → enter edit mode with overwrite (clear cell, start typing)
9. Escape → if editing: cancel; if selection: clear selection

### Step 2: Cell Selection Hook
1. Create `use-cell-selection.ts`
2. Click on cell → set activeCell, clear selectionRange
3. Shift+click → set selectionRange from activeCell to clicked cell
4. Click+drag → set start on mousedown, update end on mousemove, finalize on mouseup
5. Shift+Arrow → extend selectionRange.end in arrow direction
6. Ctrl+A → selectionRange covers all data cells
7. Normalize range: ensure start ≤ end (swap if needed)

### Step 3: Selection Rendering
1. CellRenderer checks if cell is within selectionRange → add `.selected` class
2. Active cell gets `.active` class (blue border)
3. Selection range gets light blue background
4. Use CSS only — no React state per cell for selection highlighting
5. Optimization: compute selection bounds once, pass via context or CSS custom properties

### Step 4: Clipboard Hook
1. Create `use-clipboard.ts`
2. **Copy (Ctrl+C):** Read all cell values in selectionRange → join with \t and \n → `navigator.clipboard.writeText(tsv)`
3. **Cut (Ctrl+X):** Copy + clear all cells in range
4. **Paste (Ctrl+V):** `navigator.clipboard.readText()` → split by \n and \t → write to cells starting at activeCell
5. Paste respects read-only cells (skip them)
6. Paste larger than grid: expand grid? No — truncate to existing columns (YAGNI)
7. Handle `paste` event on grid container (captures from OS clipboard)

### Step 5: Delete / Clear
1. Delete or Backspace key: clear all cells in selectionRange
2. If single cell: clear active cell
3. Batch update via meta.updateData (or HyperFormula in Phase 6)

## Todo List

- [ ] `use-keyboard-navigation.ts` — full arrow/tab/enter/home/end/pageup/down
- [ ] `use-cell-selection.ts` — click, shift+click, click+drag, shift+arrow
- [ ] `use-clipboard.ts` — copy/cut/paste in TSV format
- [ ] Attach keyboard handler to grid container
- [ ] Selection highlight rendering (CSS classes)
- [ ] Active cell distinct styling
- [ ] Delete/Backspace clear cells
- [ ] Ctrl+A select all
- [ ] F2 + typing to enter edit mode
- [ ] Paste into multi-cell area
- [ ] Keyboard scrolls viewport to keep activeCell visible

## Success Criteria
- Navigate entire grid using only keyboard (arrows, Tab, Enter)
- Select range with Shift+click and Shift+arrows
- Copy cells → paste into Excel → data matches
- Copy from Excel → paste into grid → data populates correctly
- Keyboard navigation never loses focus or causes scroll jump
- Performance: selection of 1000 cells renders highlight in <16ms

## Risk Assessment

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|--------|------------|
| Browser clipboard API permission denied | Medium | High | Fallback to document.execCommand('copy'); show toast on denial |
| Drag-select conflicts with text selection | Medium | Medium | preventDefault on mousedown in grid; user-select: none on cells |
| Paste large data causes lag | Low | Medium | Batch updates with requestAnimationFrame; suspendEvaluation in Phase 6 |

## Security Considerations
- Paste content must be sanitized — no script injection via clipboard
- TSV parsing: handle edge cases (quoted fields, embedded tabs, newlines in values)
- Clipboard API requires HTTPS in production (or localhost in dev)

## Next Steps
- Phase 6 (Formula Engine) will integrate clipboard with HyperFormula (paste formulas)
- Phase 7 (Polish) will add undo/redo for clipboard operations
</file>

