# Brainstorm: Spreadsheet Data Grid Architecture

**Date:** 2026-03-26
**Status:** Approved
**Scope:** Reusable React spreadsheet component with AG Grid-like features

---

## Problem Statement

Build a reusable, high-performance spreadsheet data grid component for React with:
- AG Grid-level features (sort, filter, edit, formulas, keyboard nav)
- shadcn/ui design system + Tailwind CSS
- TanStack Table v8 as headless logic layer
- Support for 10k-50k rows with virtualization
- Full formula engine with A1 references

## Tech Stack (Decided)

| Layer | Choice | Rationale |
|-------|--------|-----------|
| Framework | Vite + React 19 + TypeScript | SPA focus, fast dev |
| Table Logic | TanStack Table v8 | Headless, built-in sort/filter/group |
| Virtualization | TanStack Virtual | Row + column virtualization |
| UI | shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS | Accessible, consistent design |
| State | Zustand + Immer | Flat grid state, undo/redo via zundo |
| Formula Engine | HyperFormula (MIT) | 400+ Excel functions, dependency graph, A1 refs |
| DnD | @dnd-kit/core | Column/row reorder |
| Validation | Zod | Schema-per-column |
| Export | SheetJS (xlsx) | Excel + CSV |

## Feature List (27 features, 8 phases)

### P1: Core Grid (2 weeks)
1. Virtual scrolling (row + column)
2. Core table rendering (shadcn + TanStack Table)
3. Sorting (single + multi-column)
4. Filtering (per-column + global)
5. Pagination + infinite scroll

### P2: Column Management (2 weeks)
6. Column resize (drag handles)
7. Column reorder (DnD)
8. Column pin/freeze (left + right)
9. Column visibility toggle

### P3: Row Features (2 weeks)
10. Row selection (single + multi)
11. Row pinning (top + bottom)
12. Tree/hierarchical rows (expand/collapse)
13. Row grouping

### P4: Cell Editing (2 weeks)
14. Inline cell editing
15. Cell validation (Zod)
16. Cell types (text, number, date, select, checkbox)

### P5: Keyboard & Clipboard (2 weeks)
17. Keyboard navigation (arrows, Tab, Enter, Home/End)
18. Multi-cell selection (click+drag, Shift+click)
19. Copy/Paste (TSV clipboard format)

### P6: Formula Engine (2-3 weeks)
20. HyperFormula integration
21. Formula bar UI
22. A1 cell references
23. Auto-fill (drag handle)

### P7: Polish (2 weeks)
24. Undo/Redo (zundo + HyperFormula sync)
25. CSV/Excel export
26. Context menu
27. Cell formatting (bold, color, alignment)

### P8: Component API (1 week)
28. Props API design
29. Storybook documentation
30. Package publish prep

## Architecture

### Component Tree
```
<SpreadsheetProvider>       ← Zustand store
  <Toolbar />               ← Formatting actions
  <FormulaBar />            ← Active cell formula
  <SheetGrid>
    <ColumnHeaders />       ← Resizable, reorderable, pinnable
    <RowNumbers />          ← Row index
    <VirtualGrid>           ← TanStack Virtual viewport
      <PinnedRows top />
      <PinnedCols left />
      <CellRenderer />     ← Display vs edit mode
      <PinnedCols right />
      <PinnedRows bottom />
    </VirtualGrid>
  </SheetGrid>
  <StatusBar />             ← Selection info
  <ContextMenu />           ← Right-click (Portal)
</SpreadsheetProvider>
```

### State Design (Zustand)
- `cells: Record<string, CellData>` — O(1) cell access
- `columns: ColumnDef[]` — column config
- `activeCell / selectionRange` — selection state
- `editingCell / editValue` — edit mode
- `pinnedColumns / pinnedRows` — pin config
- `expandedRows: Set<string>` — tree state
- `history` — undo/redo via zundo middleware

### Key Decisions
1. **HyperFormula owns cell values**, Zustand owns UI state — single source of truth
2. **Pinned rows/cols render outside virtual container** — avoids scroll conflicts
3. **Cell memoization** via React.memo + shallow compare on value + format
4. **Keyboard handler** at grid container level, delegates to active cell
5. **Copy/Paste** uses TSV format (Excel-compatible)

## Risks

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| HyperFormula ~200KB bundle | Lazy load / code split |
| Zustand-HyperFormula sync | HyperFormula = value source, Zustand = UI source |
| Pinned + virtual scroll glitches | Separate fixed containers |
| 50k rows + formula recalc | Web Worker for HyperFormula |
| Component API bloat | Minimal props, expand on demand |

## Timeline

~15-17 weeks total for full v1 with all features.

## Next Steps

Create detailed implementation plan with phase files.
</file>

